		<description>Caliber: 4.85x49mm. 20-round detachable mag. Select-Fire.
		
This is a Colt Model 601 (M16) rifle converted to 4.85x49mm caliber, the same round developed for the Enfield XL60 and XL70 series in the United Kingdom. The original rifle, serial number 202715, had been acquired sometime around 1965, still chambered in .223/5.56, and was used during the Borneo confrontation. In 1967 it was tested in order to obtain "ejection paths, noise levels and recoil kinematics using ball &amp; sample blanks" using M193 Remington ball ammo. Circa 1970, the same rifle was converted to the 4.85mm round as part of NATO ammunition trials.</description>
